<item>
            <title>[LU-10408] sanityn test_32b: lockless i/o works when disabled</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-10408</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This issue was created by maloo for John Hammond &amp;lt;john.hammond@intel.com&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This issue relates to the following test suite run: &lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.hpdd.intel.com/test_sets/31746e2a-e444-11e7-8027-52540065bddc&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.hpdd.intel.com/test_sets/31746e2a-e444-11e7-8027-52540065bddc&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The sub-test test_32b failed with the following error:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;lockless i/o works when disabled
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The failure report indicated that this was introduced by &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/30063/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/30063/&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-9019&quot; title=&quot;Migrate lustre to standard 64 bit time kernel API&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-9019&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-9019&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; osc: migrate to time64_t&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;See &lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.hpdd.intel.com/sub_tests/query?utf8=%E2%9C%93&amp;amp;test_set%5Btest_set_script_id%5D=570ba67a-4a46-11e0-a7f6-52540025f9af&amp;amp;sub_test%5Bsub_test_script_id%5D=5aa744f6-4a46-11e0-a7f6-52540025f9af&amp;amp;status%5B%5D=FAIL&amp;amp;query_bugs=&amp;amp;warn%5Bnotice%5D=false&amp;amp;builds=&amp;amp;hosts=&amp;amp;gerrit=&amp;amp;test_session%5Btest_group%5D%5B%5D=&amp;amp;test_session%5Buser_id%5D%5B%5D=&amp;amp;test_session%5Bquery_recent_period%5D=&amp;amp;test_session%5Bstart_date%5D=2017-11-01&amp;amp;test_session%5Bend_date%5D=&amp;amp;test_node%5Bos_type_id%5D=&amp;amp;test_node%5Bdistribution_type_id%5D=&amp;amp;test_node%5Barchitecture_type_id%5D=&amp;amp;test_node%5Bfile_system_type_id%5D=&amp;amp;test_node%5Blustre_branch_id%5D=&amp;amp;test_node_network%5Bnetwork_type_id%5D=&amp;amp;commit=Update+results&amp;amp;num_results=50&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.hpdd.intel.com/sub_tests/query?utf8=%E2%9C%93&amp;amp;test_set%5Btest_set_script_id%5D=570ba67a-4a46-11e0-a7f6-52540025f9af&amp;amp;sub_test%5Bsub_test_script_id%5D=5aa744f6-4a46-11e0-a7f6-52540025f9af&amp;amp;status%5B%5D=FAIL&amp;amp;query_bugs=&amp;amp;warn%5Bnotice%5D=false&amp;amp;builds=&amp;amp;hosts=&amp;amp;gerrit=&amp;amp;test_session%5Btest_group%5D%5B%5D=&amp;amp;test_session%5Buser_id%5D%5B%5D=&amp;amp;test_session%5Bquery_recent_period%5D=&amp;amp;test_session%5Bstart_date%5D=2017-11-01&amp;amp;test_session%5Bend_date%5D=&amp;amp;test_node%5Bos_type_id%5D=&amp;amp;test_node%5Bdistribution_type_id%5D=&amp;amp;test_node%5Barchitecture_type_id%5D=&amp;amp;test_node%5Bfile_system_type_id%5D=&amp;amp;test_node%5Blustre_branch_id%5D=&amp;amp;test_node_network%5Bnetwork_type_id%5D=&amp;amp;commit=Update+results&amp;amp;num_results=50&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;



